#: ../../source/concepts/asyncio.rst:11 fc68e4633ab64d2f89e2f311c03b6ca8
msgid "What's asyncio?"
msgstr "什么是 asyncio？"

#: ../../source/concepts/asyncio.rst:13 d30f81618fb8480b8735fecc4fb1ea59
msgid ""
"`asyncio`_ is a Python 3's built-in library. This means it's already "
"installed if you have Python 3. Since Python 3.5, it is convenient to "
"work with asynchronous code. Before (Python 3.4) we didn't have ``async``"
" or ``await``, but now we do."
msgstr ""
"`asyncio` 是 Python 3 的一个标准库。这意味着当你安装了 Python 3，"
"它就已经安装好了。自 Python 3.5 以来，使用异步代码变得非常方便。"
"在以前（Python 3.4 之前），我们没有 ``async``, ``await``，但现在有了。"

#: ../../source/concepts/asyncio.rst:17 b8c76f66853340ad8c2806a466493183
msgid ""
"`asyncio`_ stands for *Asynchronous Input Output*. This is a very powerful"
" concept to use whenever you work IO. Interacting with the web or "
"external APIs such as Telegram's makes a lot of sense this way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/asyncio.rst:23 71b9f4b75cfd46a28e2476d5b7a87308
msgid "Why asyncio?"
msgstr "为什么要使用 asyncio？"

#: ../../source/concepts/asyncio.rst:25 0612896b47754fe0aacf82d08eed9b43
msgid ""
"Asynchronous IO makes a lot of sense in a library like Telethon. You send"
" a request to the server (such as \"get some message\"), and thanks to "
"`asyncio`_, your code won't block while a response arrives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/asyncio.rst:29 a980259db0a0405eab17a20b5afaa1e3
msgid ""
"The alternative would be to spawn a thread for each update so that other "
"code can run while the response arrives. That is *a lot* more expensive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/asyncio.rst:33 61e0c59b73be4c67bd65650ffe1f3bf2
msgid ""
"The code will also run faster, because instead of switching back and "
"forth between the OS and your script, your script can handle it all. "
"Avoiding switching saves quite a bit of time, in Python or any other "
"language that supports asynchronous IO. It will also be cheaper, because "
"tasks are smaller than threads, which are smaller than processes."
msgstr ""

